.TH "tomoyo_path_perm" 9 "tomoyo_path_perm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tomoyo_path_perm \- Check permission for "unlink", "rmdir", "truncate", "symlink", "append", "chroot" and "unmount".
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tomoyo_path_perm
.BI "(const u8 operation "  ","
.BI "const struct path *path "  ","
.BI "const char *target "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "operation" 12
Type of operation.
.IP "path" 12
Pointer to "struct path".
.IP "target" 12
Symlink's target if \fIoperation\fP is TOMOYO_TYPE_SYMLINK,
NULL otherwise.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, negative value otherwise.
